{"key":"post-9672386","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9672386</id>\n<content>The series 1 from FP is a great filter.&amp;nbsp; I've had mine since he first started making them.&amp;nbsp; You can do large spawn bags, but you'll have to lay them on their sides and do one at a time, because that's all it has room for.&amp;nbsp; If you can afford it, a 24 X 24 will allow you to do ten or more at once, because you can have them open while standing up.&amp;nbsp; Since your PC only holds two, the 12 X 24 will work fine.&amp;nbsp; Don't forget to use a pre-filter.&amp;nbsp; I have since new, and am still on the original HEPA after just over ten years.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I can stack 8 large folded spawn bags in front of the filter to cool, and then open one at a time in front of the hood.&amp;nbsp; If I'm doing more than that, I stick them inside tyvek coveralls and zip them up.&amp;nbsp; Tie the sleeves and legs with knots and fold the hood into the zipper and you can leave them there for a week or more and be safe, especially if you PC them with tyvek sleeves inside the way I show in the sawdust/woodchip section on the DVD.&lt;br /&gt;RR&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/files/05-23/838197699-flow_hood_003a.jpg&quot; class=&quot;highslide&quot; onclick=&quot;return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;/forums/thumbs/05-23/838197699-thumb_flow_hood_003a.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9672996</next>\n<prev>9671623</prev>\n<first>9671623</first>\n<last>9674104</last>\n<when>1232845029</when>\n<utime>01/25/09 02:57 AM</utime>\n</post>"}